author: cbs8
title: New Orleans man dies in St. Bernard Parish boating accident
text:
CHALMETTE, La. (AP) - State agents say a 66-year-old New Orleans man died after he fell from a fishing boat in St. Bernard Parish.
The Louisiana Department of Wildlife and Fisheries said in a news release Ernest Owens was found unresponsive after authorities were called to Daylight Bay about 11 a.m. Tuesday.
State officials say a 64-year-old Meraux man told investigators that the two men were fishing and Owens fell from their 18-foot-boat as he was trying to tie it to a barge.
Search crews took the men to a nearby marina, where Owens was pronounced dead.
The agency says neither man was wearing a personal flotation device.
